</table></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uscirocco.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Scirocco</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>FAQ/Index Moderator</span><br> <font color=#333399>(8/15/01 8:44:08 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: killing Talendor</span><hr size=1> A few pointers to killing Talendor.<br>
<br>
First, he is usually found along the western wall of the zone, about halfway up near the VP zone entrance.  He has a large aggro range.<br>
<br>
Second, set up your tank and caster teams around the mouth of the gorge leading to the BW zone.  It doesn't really matter where in that area, as long as you are south of the mob pathing.  If your teams will get feared a lot, set up further down in the gorge closer to the zone, to reduce the possibility of adds and to limit running area.  FR and MR are the most important, as noted above. Since this is a popular camping area, shout out to the zone that Tal is being pulled to the BW zone in X minutes to allow folks a chance to wrap things up and move to safe ground.<br>
<br>
Third, pulling is pretty easy if you are KOS to Talendor.  I usually do it for my guild.  I am in wolf form, levitating, and invis.  Many of the mobs in the pulling area will not see invis, although the higher level mobs up near Talendor may.  Invis. is key, as Talendor will be able to aggro on you when you move into his large range as he sees invis, but the other mobs in the area will still not see you.  Pick up Talendor on tracking (you will most likely be able to do this about a third of the way up the zone wall), and head towards him.  Make sure your raid is ready for him.  Con the mobs you see as you move to make sure they can't see you.  When you see Talendor at a distance, you are close to being in aggro range.  If you see him moving towards you, or if you hear his shout, you are in aggro range.  Turn south and run, pulling him while you remain invisible.<br>
<br>
Fourth, shout your progress as you get close to the tanks.  This allows last minutes buffs to be put up, like the mage's fire shield. Run through the tanks with Talendor behind you.  Talendor should stop and make friends with the tanks at this point, since your aggro priority is low.  The tanks pound while the clerics heal.  The casters come in when he drops to about 50% to 70% in health (depends on your raid makeup, of course).<br>
<br>
Fifth, be aware of the fire DoT after the kill, as noted above.  More people get killed because of that than during the actual fight. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ugroovydancepants.showPublicProfile?language=EN>GroovyDancepants</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(8/15/01 3:59:41 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: killing Talendor</span><hr size=1> Bark potions are for lewsers!<br>
<br>
We tend to use a dictated 51ish mob from the named cycle or a mature wurm as a tank. Now that they changed pet aggro we'll see if it continues to work. I suppose you could root him and force him to tank while your buddies are feared. If your tanks resist the first fear, have them go full offensive disc, but not before.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uainalda.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ainalda</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_star.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(8/15/01 11:20:37 pm)</font><br>     <br>Community Supporter<br> <BR><img src=http://www.aredhel.ch/eq/atk.jpg width=103 height=100></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: killing Talendor</span><hr size=1> thanks Scirocco ^_^ <p><table width="489" border="0" cellspacing="2" cellpadding="2">
